==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shiah
<hw>Shi"ah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. <ets>sh⟦imac⟧'a⟦imac⟧</ets>a follower of
the sect of Ali, fr. <ets>sh⟦imac⟧'at</ets>, <ets>sh⟦imac⟧'ah</ets>, a
multitude following one another in pursuit of the same object, the sect
of Ali, fr. <ets>sh⟦amac⟧'a</ets> to follow.]</ety> <def>A member of
that branch of the Mohammedans to which the Persians belong. They reject
the first three caliphs, and consider Ali as being the first and only
rightful successor of Mohammed. They do not acknowledge the Sunna, or
body of traditions respecting Mohammed, as any part of the law, and on
these accounts are treated as heretics by the Sunnites, or orthodox
Mohammedans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

